
mixin MongoDBAccordion

  .accordion#accordionExample
    //- each item,index in items
    .accordion-item
      h2.accordion-header(id=`heading1`)
        button.accordion-button(type='button' class=(index > 0 && 'collapsed') data-bs-toggle='collapse' data-bs-target=`#collapse1` aria-expanded='true' aria-controls=`collapse1`)
          | MongoDB
      .accordion-collapse.collapse(class=(index === 0 && 'show')  id=`collapse1` aria-labelledby=`heading1` data-bs-parent='#accordionExample')
        h5.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center  To create a MongoDB connection follow these steps:
        ul
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center Log in to your MongoDB Atlas account.
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center From the Atlas dashboard, select your project.
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center In the left-hand navigation pane, click on &quot;Database Access&quot; under the &quot;Security&quot; section.
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center Click the &quot;Add New Database User&quot; button.
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center Enter a username and password for the new user. Make sure to use a strong password.
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center Choose the desired authentication method. You can select either &quot;Password&quot; or &quot;AWS IAM Database Authentication&quot; depending on your requirements. For most cases, the &quot;Password&quot; option is appropriate.
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center Under the &quot;Database User Privileges&quot; section, you can define the user's privileges. Select the appropriate role or roles based on the user's access requirements. You can choose from existing roles or create a custom role with specific privileges.
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center Click the &quot;Add User&quot; button to create the user.
          li
            h6.mb-0.mt-2.mb-2.ml-2.d-flex.align-items-center Enter the username, password and cluster in the fields below.
          input(type="text" placeholder='username').mt-2
          input(type="text" placeholder='password').mt-2
          input(type="text" placeholder='cluster').mt-2
          button(type='button').btn.ml-2.btn-falcon-default.btn-sm Create
        